						<summary>

						<p>The inscription has the introduction commencing with <hi rend="italic">Pūmādu puṇara</hi> etc. It is mutilated at the beginning. It records a gift of 11 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> deposited with the temple authorities of Kālakāladēvar, for burning with the interest thereon a perpetual lamp before the deity, by one Rājarāja-Munaiyadaraśar a resident of Iḷaṅgārikuḍi in Rājanārāyaṇa vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
